column5: Spent part of the day, yesterday, visiting with the daughter. Of course, brought the rods and headed to Bayfront. Bite was slow, but we managed a few fish, cats and suckers. photobucket is acting up, but problem solved.
nice lookin' day and a couple fish
You had a great day to be out on the shorelines Bruce Great report and pics Thanks for sharing Jacques
i've seen lots of those cats but never seen a sucker come out of there
Good stuff Bruce...i've only ever caught a sucker once...about the same size as your picture....but man did it put up a good fight!  cheers for the report.  Simon
goodjob man, i was actually at that exact spot last friday lol
hmmmm, well apparently my original post is gone sooooo......   nice lookin' day and a couple fish
Nice job. I gotta get down there
Good going Bruce.A few minnows at the #3 pic spot will produce a few surprises,LOL.

Was down there for a little while this evening, and there was nothing going on. Got a Goby, saw a sucker and a tiny little Bluegill, but they were'nt having any of it... Been a long time since I fished here, now I remember why! LOL...
Great report! Nothings better than fishing with family!
Spent some time with family, got outdoors and fished for a while, caught some fish, nice day at waters edge. Looks like a banner day to me.  Cheers !
Hey Bruce, is that the type of sucker u can use for catfish cutbait and did ya keep it ? Good to see Anna and friend still likes fishing.
I think the girls would have been a bit Eewwww like   Did strictly C&R for the outing.
Nice fish and thanks for the report.
nice fish man, looked like fun
